#8220;While the world is still early in its embrace of Web3, it is a market that is already demonstrating tremendous potential with many customers asking us to increase our support for Web3 and crypto-related technologies.&#8221;<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Along with leading marketing initiatives, some of the duties required for the position consist of building Web 3.0 yearly plans and increasing awareness among various groups of the Web 3.0 audience. <\/span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">The position is offered in New York, San Francisco, Seattle, and Sunnyvale only. This is Google&#8217;s first time seeking into Web 3.0, nonetheless being known to launch and abandon various internal actions.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2>Gavin Wood&#8217;s Opinion on Web 3.0<\/h2>\n<p><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/polkadot-price-prediction-2022\/\">Polkadot (DOT)<\/a> founder Gavin Wood discussed the growth of Web 3.0 with Cointelegraph during the World Economic Forum (WEF) Annual Meeting 2022. Web 3.0 apps do not need to expand beyond their current usage, according to Wood:<\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&#8220;I don&#8217;t think Web3 needs to evolve, really, from its origins too much yet, but maybe in the future, it will.&#8221;<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Wood also discussed how Web 3.0 expanded the discourse beyond <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-bitcoin\/\">Bitcoin (BTC)<\/a>, smart contracts, and <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-decentralized-finance\/\">decentralized finance (DeFi)<\/a> to the core technology that runs the crypto world.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-acad